Pre-Game Insights: Pakistan will play their eighth match of the 2023 World Cup against New Zealand on November 4, 2023, at the M Chinnaswamy Stadium in Bengaluru.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Pakistan and New Zealand have faced off 115 times in ODIs, with Pakistan winning 60 matches.The match is expected to be a competitive contest, with New Zealand starting as favorites but Pakistan showing recent form.The match will be broadcasted in several countries, including India on Star Sports/Disney+ Hotstar and the USA on Willow TV/ESPN+.The historical rivalry between Pakistan and New Zealand adds context to the match.
